    },
    {
      "step_id": "8ae2c85d",
      "step_index": 4,
      "step_type": "reasoning",
      "content": "### 3) CONSIDER mechanistic basis (interaction with CYP2D6)\n- Likely binds as a **reversible competitive inhibitor**:\n  - **Protonated tertiary amine** anchors via ionic interaction to the enzyme\u2019s acidic site.\n  - **Aromatic rings/CF3** fill hydrophobic regions, stabilizing binding orientation.\n- The heteroaromatic nitrogens can contribute **additional H-bond acceptor interactions** and influence binding pose.\n- This scaffold also resembles many \u201cCNS-like\u201d basic aromatic compounds that frequently show **CYP2D6 inhibition**.",
